        <div class="case-study-hero-image">
            <img src="/porto-massage-studio.svg" alt="Porto Massage Studio landing page preview">
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Overview Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>Porto Massage Studio is a wellness center in Porto offering various massage and relaxation services. They needed a professional online presence that would showcase their services, facilitate customer inquiries, and establish credibility with potential clients.</p>

        <p>The challenge was creating a landing page that would serve multiple purposes: present their range of services clearly, enable easy contact, showcase their expertise, and work seamlessly on mobile devices where most of their traffic originates.</p>

        <p>The result is a clean, conversion-focused landing page that highlights their service offerings, builds trust with social proof, and makes booking a session as simple as one click.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Challenge Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section gray-bg">
        <h2>The Challenge</h2>

        <div class="challenge-content">
            <h3>The Situation</h3>
            <p>Porto Massage Studio faced several key challenges with their online presence:</p>

            <ul class="challenge-list">
                <li><strong>No Online Presence:</strong> The studio relied entirely on walk-ins and word-of-mouth, missing potential online clients who wanted to learn about their services.</li>
                <li><strong>Limited Contact Options:</strong> Clients had to call during business hours to inquire about services, creating friction in the initial contact process.</li>
                <li><strong>Service Clarity:</strong> Potential clients couldn't easily understand the different massage types and services offered without visiting in person.</li>
                <li><strong>Mobile Accessibility:</strong> Most inquiries came from mobile devices, but they had no mobile-optimized presence.</li>
                <li><strong>Trust Building:</strong> Without online reviews or professional presentation, they struggled to convert first-time clients.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Goals</h3>
            <ul class="goals-list">
                <li>Create a professional landing page within 2 weeks</li>
                <li>Showcase services with clear descriptions and pricing</li>
                <li>Enable multiple contact options (WhatsApp, phone, form)</li>
                <li>Optimize for mobile users (primary audience)</li>
                <li>Build trust with social proof and testimonials</li>
                <li>Include basic SEO for local discoverability</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Solution Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section">
        <h2>The Solution</h2>

        <h3>Discovery & Strategy</h3>
        <p>I started by researching Porto Massage Studio's target audience and competitors. Most wellness centers in Porto had outdated websites or relied solely on social media. This was an opportunity to stand out with a modern, professional landing page.</p>

        <p>The strategy focused on three key principles:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Calming aesthetic:</strong> Soft colors, generous whitespace, and serene imagery to reflect the relaxation experience</li>
            <li><strong>Service clarity:</strong> Clear service cards with descriptions, durations, and pricing for each massage type</li>
            <li><strong>Conversion optimization:</strong> Strategic placement of contact CTAs throughout the page</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Implementation</h3>
        <p>During the two-week development period, I implemented:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Design & Structure:</strong> Clean landing page with calming aesthetic (soft blues, warm neutrals) and mobile-first design</li>
            <li><strong>Technical SEO:</strong> Optimized meta tags, LocalBusiness schema markup, and fast page speed (0.9s)</li>
            <li><strong>Content:</strong> Detailed service cards with descriptions, durations, benefits, and pricing for each massage type</li>
            <li><strong>Features:</strong> Contact forms with email notifications, direct WhatsApp button, and embedded Google Maps</li>
            <li><strong>Social Proof:</strong> Client testimonial section to build trust and showcase previous client experiences</li>
            <li><strong>Mobile Optimization:</strong> Touch-friendly buttons, fast loading on mobile networks, and optimized images</li>
            <li><strong>Testing & Launch:</strong> Thorough testing across devices and browsers, with analytics tracking</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Features Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section gray-bg">
        <h2>Key Features</h2>

        <h3>Service Showcase</h3>
        <p>Each massage service has its own section with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Service name and description</li>
            <li>Duration and pricing</li>
            <li>Benefits and what to expect</li>
            <li>Direct booking CTA</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Multiple Contact Options</h3>
        <p>Made booking effortless with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>WhatsApp Button:</strong> One-click to start conversation</li>
            <li><strong>Click-to-Call:</strong> Direct phone calling on mobile</li>
            <li><strong>Contact Form:</strong> Simple form for those who prefer email</li>
            <li><strong>Location Map:</strong> Embedded Google Maps for easy navigation</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Social Proof & Trust</h3>
        <p>Built credibility with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Client testimonial section showcasing experiences</li>
            <li>Google Reviews integration (5.0 rating, 78 reviews)</li>
            <li>Professional photography of treatment spaces</li>
            <li>Years of experience highlighted</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Mobile Optimization</h3>
        <p>Perfect mobile experience with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Touch-friendly buttons and navigation</li>
            <li>Fast loading on mobile networks (0.9s)</li>
            <li>Readable typography without zooming</li>
            <li>Optimized images that load quickly</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Technical SEO Foundation</h3>
        <p>Set up for local discoverability:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Optimized title and meta descriptions</li>
            <li>LocalBusiness schema markup</li>
            <li>96/100 PageSpeed score</li>
            <li>Mobile-friendly (Google's #1 ranking factor)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Results Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section">
        <h2>Results</h2>

        <h3>Project Delivery</h3>
        <div class="results-grid">
            <div class="result-item">
                <div class="result-category">Timeline</div>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Delivered on time</strong> - exactly 2 weeks from start to launch</li>
                    <li><strong>3 revision rounds</strong> included in timeline</li>
                    <li><strong>Same-day fixes</strong> for post-launch adjustments</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="result-item">
                <div class="result-category">Technical Performance</div>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>96/100 PageSpeed</strong> score on mobile</li>
                    <li><strong>0.9s load time</strong> on 4G connection</li>
                    <li><strong>100% mobile-friendly</strong> per Google's test</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="result-item">
                <div class="result-category">Client Impact</div>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Professional credibility</strong> - enhanced brand perception</li>
                    <li><strong>24/7 inquiries</strong> - enabled anytime customer contact</li>
                    <li><strong>Reduced phone calls</strong> - comprehensive service information online</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3>What the Client Said</h3>
        <blockquote class="testimonial">
            <p>"The landing page exceeded our expectations. It's beautiful, easy to use, and we're getting inquiries from clients who would never have called us before. The mobile experience is perfect."</p>
            <cite>— Joaquim Marco, Porto Massage Studio</cite>
        </blockquote>
    </section>

    <!-- Technologies Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section gray-bg">
        <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
        <ul class="tech-list">
            <li><strong>Astro:</strong> Static site generator for maximum performance</li>
            <li><strong>CSS3:</strong> Modern CSS for responsive design</li>
            <li><strong>Google Maps API:</strong> Location integration</li>
            <li><strong>Schema.org:</strong> LocalBusiness structured data</li>
            <li><strong>Formspree:</strong> Contact form handling</li>
            <li><strong>Vercel:</strong> Fast, reliable hosting with global CDN</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Lessons Learned Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section">
        <h2>Lessons Learned</h2>
        <p>This project reinforced several key principles for landing page projects:</p>

        <ol class="lessons-list">
            <li><strong>Mobile-first is critical for service businesses:</strong> With 80% of inquiries from mobile devices, designing mobile-first ensured the best experience for the majority.</li>
            <li><strong>Service clarity drives conversions:</strong> Clear, detailed service descriptions with benefits and pricing eliminated pre-booking questions and reduced back-and-forth communication.</li>
            <li><strong>Multiple contact options matter:</strong> Different people prefer different contact methods. Offering WhatsApp, phone, and email maximizes conversion.</li>
            <li><strong>Visual aesthetics must match brand promise:</strong> The calming design aesthetic reinforced the relaxation experience clients expect.</li>
            <li><strong>Social proof builds trust:</strong> Testimonials and Google Reviews integration helped convert first-time visitors into clients.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Section -->
    <section class="cta-section">
        <h2>NEED A LANDING PAGE?</h2>
        <p>If you're a service business looking for a professional, conversion-focused landing page delivered quickly, I can help.</p>
        <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary">GET YOUR LANDING PAGE</a>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Projects Section -->
    <section class="related-projects">
        <h2>Related Projects</h2>
        <div class="related-projects-grid">
            <a href="/projects/brunno-rodrigues" class="related-project-card">
                <img src="/brunno-rodrigues.svg" alt="Brunno Rodrigues website">
                <h3>Brunno Rodrigues</h3>
                <p>Landing page for massage therapist</p>
            </a>
            <a href="/projects/porto-car-care" class="related-project-card">
                <img src="/final fnal final.svg" alt="Porto Car Care website">
                <h3>Porto Car Care</h3>
                <p>Local SEO case study with 3× visibility growth</p>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <script>
        // Mobile Menu Toggle
        const mobileMenuToggle = document.querySelector('.mobile-menu-toggle');
        const navLinks = document.querySelector('.nav-links');

        if (mobileMenuToggle) {
            mobileMenuToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
                mobileMenuToggle.classList.toggle('active');
                navLinks.classList.toggle('active');
            });

            const links = navLinks.querySelectorAll('a');
            links.forEach(link => {
                link.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    mobileMenuToggle.classList.remove('active');
                    navLinks.classList.remove('active');
                });
            });
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>

<style>
/* Reset & Base Styles */
